## Terms Table
<!-- Define all project-specific, technical, business, AI, and regulatory terms used in project artefacts. Keep definitions precise — avoid circular definitions. -->
| Term | Definition | Category | Source |
|------|-----------|----------|--------|
| Requirements Baseline | The formally approved, frozen set of requirements at a specific point in time. Any post-freeze change requires a formal Change Request. | Technical | Phase 2 Methodology |
| Acceptance Criterion | A specific, testable condition that a requirement must satisfy to be considered complete. Written in Given/When/Then format. | Technical | Phase 2 Methodology |
| RTM (see Acronyms) | A matrix that maps each requirement to its acceptance criteria and test cases, ensuring full traceability from requirement to test. | Technical | Phase 2 Methodology |
| NFR (see Acronyms) | A requirement that describes system quality attributes — such as performance, security, scalability, and availability — rather than specific behaviours. | Technical | Phase 2 Methodology |
| Gate B | The formal phase gate at the end of Phase 2. Requires all requirements artefacts to be complete, RTM coverage at 100%, and stakeholder sign-off before Phase 3 begins. | Technical | Phase 2 Methodology |
